title indicates, the plays were translated to capture the vivacity of performances on stage. The translations, each accompanied by a thorough introduction that contextualizes the play, are based not only on published texts, but performance scripts and the study of the plays as they are performed in theatres today. Each volume is lavishly illustrated with rare woodblock prints in full color of Tokugawa- and Meiji-period productions as well as color and black-and-white photographs of contemporary performances.Published with the assistance of the Nippon Foundation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aHISTORY / Asia / Japan.2bisacsh1 aBrandon, James R., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrandon, James R., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aIshikiri, Kajiwara Heizö Homare no, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKagami, Natsu Matsuri Naniwa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeiter, Samuel L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeiter, Samuel L., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aM, Domo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMonogatari, Sanemori, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMusume, Sagi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNijushikö, Honchö, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTaimen, Kotobuki Soga no, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aUri, Uirö, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Hawaii Press eBook-Package Backlist 2000-2015z978311066325940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978082484246840u